$ COM related methods in the System..Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal class

Some(!) → Windows/development/COM related methods in → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Runtime/InteropServices/Marshal[`System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal`] include
  • `AddRef` and its counterpart `Release`
  • `GetComInterfaceForObject` (returns `IntPtr`)
  • `GetIUnknownForObject` (returns `IntPtr`)
  • `GetIDispatchForObject` (returns `IntPtr`)
  • `QueryInterface`
  • `AllocCoTaskMem`
  • `GetEndComSlot`
  • `IsComObject`
  • `GetObjectForIUnknown` (returns `Object`)

Some `GetXXX` methods return an → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/IntPtr[`System.IntPtr`] that represents an → Windows/development/COM/IUnknown[`IUnknown`] interface.
-
The `AddRef` and `Release` methods require such a pointer in their argument.
